data.enText: a large organ in the body that cleans the blood and produces bile
the liver of some animals that is cooked and eaten

tr: large and complicated reddish-brown glandular organ located in the upper right portion of the abdominal cavity
secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat
synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood
detoxifies poisonous substances and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes
liver of an animal used as meat
someone who lives in a place
a person who has a special life style

value.def: Your liver is a large organ in your body which processes your blood and helps to clean unwanted substances out of it.
Liver is the liver of some animals, especially lambs, pigs, and cows, which is cooked and eaten.
value.tran: （尤指猪、牛、羊等动物供食用的）肝

trans: 肝功；肝功能；肝功能检查；肝功能试验；肝脏功能
肝功能检查；肝功能测验
